  orderNo 18
  title `Common High Court for Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura, Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39855&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be a common High Court for the States of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur,`
  line `Tripura, Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh to be called the Gauhati High Court (the High Court of`
  line `Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura, Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh) (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the common High Court);`
  line
  line `(b) the Judges of the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and`
  line `Mizoram holding office immediately before that day shall, unless they have elected otherwise,`
  line `become on that day the Judges of the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenditure in respect of the salaries and allowances of the Judges of the common High Court`
  line `shall be allocated amongst the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram,`
  line `Nagaland and Tripura in such proportion as the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39822)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Provision as to advocates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39822&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), in section 3, in sub-section (1), for clause (b), the`
  line `following clause shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(b) for the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland`
  line `and Tripura to be known as the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura,`
  line `Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh;";`
  line
  line `(b) the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram shall be`
  line `deemed to be the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura, Mizoram and`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who, immediately before the appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practise in the`
  line `High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram shall be entitled to practise`
  line `as an advocate in the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) All persons who, immediately before the appointed day, are advocates on the roll of the Bar`
  line `Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram shall, as from that day, become`
  line `advocates on the roll of the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura, Mizoram`
  line `and Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(4) The right of audience in the common High Court shall be regulated in accordance with the like`
  line `principles as, immediately before the appointed day, are in force with respect to the right of audience in`
  line `the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram:`
  line
  line `Provided that as among the Advocates-General of the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur,`
  line `Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland and Tripura, the right of audience shall be determined with reference to`
  line `their dates of enrolment as advocates.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39823)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Practice and procedure in the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39823&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the`
  line `law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High`
  line `Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram shall, with the necessary`
  line `modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39824)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Custody of Seal of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39824&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day with respect to the custody of the Seal of the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya,`
  line `Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the custody`
  line `of the Seal of the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39825)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39825&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day`
  line `with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of`
  line `Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram shall, with necessary modifications, apply`
  line `with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39826)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39826&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court of Assam, Nagaland,`
  line `Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram and with respect to all matters, ancillary to the exercise of`
  line `those powers shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39827)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Principal seat and other places of sitting of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39827&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The principal seat`
  line `of the common High Court shall be at the same place at which the principal seat of the High Court of`
  line `Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram is located immediately before the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may, by notified order, provide for the establishment of a permanent bench or`
  line `benches of the common High Court at one or more places within the territories to which the jurisdiction`
  line `of the High Court extends, other than the principal seat of the High Court, and for any matters connected`
  line `therewith:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any order under this sub-section, the President shall consult the Chief`
  line `Justice of the common High Court and the Governor of the State in which the bench or benches is or are`
  line `proposed to be established.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub- section (2), the Judges and division`
  line `courts of the common High Court may also sit at such other place or places in the States of Assam,`
  line `Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura, Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh as the Chief Justice may, with`
  line `the approval of the Governor of the State concerned, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39828)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39828&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court of Assam, Nagaland,`
  line `Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram and the Judges and division courts thereof shall, with the`
  line `necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39856)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Transfer of proceedings from the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram to the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39856&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) All proceedings pending in the High Court of`
  line `Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram immediately before the appointed day`
  line `shall, from such day, stand transferred to the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding transferred under sub-section (1) shall be disposed of by the common High`
  line `Court as if such proceeding was entertained by that High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39830)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39830&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of section 26,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a court until that court has disposed of all issues`
  line `between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings`
  line `and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for`
  line `review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs; and`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division`
  line `court thereof; and references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39831)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Right to appear or to act in proceedings transferred to the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39831&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `person who, immediately before the appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of`
  line `Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur, Tripura and Mizoram and was authorised to appear or to act in`
  line `any proceedings transferred from the said High Court to the common High Court under section 26 shall`
  line `have the right to appear or to act, as the case may be, in the common High Court in relation to those`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39832)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39832&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the common High Court of any`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to any provision that may be made`
  line `on or after the appointed day with respect to that High Court by any Legislature or other authority having`
  line `power to make such provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39833)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Authorisation of expenditure pending its sanction by the Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39833&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President`
  line `may, at any time before the appointed day, authorise by order such expenditure from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the State of Arunachal Pradesh as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months`
  line `beginning with the appointed day, pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of the State of Arunachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Arunachal Pradesh may, after the appointed day, authorise by order`
  line `such further expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Arunachal`
  line `Pradesh for any period not extending beyond the said period of six months.`
  line
  line `(2) The President or, as the case may be, the Governor of Arunachal Pradesh shall make separate`
  line `orders under sub-section (1) in respect of periods falling in different financial years.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39834)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Reports relating to the accounts of the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39834&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The reports of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India referred to in section 49 of the Government`
  line `of Union Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963), relating to the accounts of the exising Union territory of`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh in respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be submitted to the Governor`
  line `of Arunachal Pradesh who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor may, by order,—`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of the existing Union territory`
  line `of Arunachal Pradesh on any service in respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the`
  line `financial year 1986-87 or in respect of any earlier financial year in excess of the amount granted for`
  line `that service and for that year as disclosed in the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been`
  line `duly authorised, and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39835)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Allowances and privileges of Governor of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39835&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The allowances and`
  line `privileges of the Governor of Arunachal Pradesh shall, until, the Governors (Emoluments, Allowances`
  line `and Privileges) Act, 1982 (43 of 1982), comes into force, be such as the President may, by order,`
  line determine.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39836)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39836&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The President shall, by order, determine the grants-in-aid of the`
  line `revenues of the State of Arunachal Pradesh and the share of that State in the Union duties of excise, estate duty and taxes on income and for that purpose amend thereby the relevant provisions of the Additional`
  line `Duties of Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), the Union Duties of Excise`
  line `(Distribution) Act, 1979 (24 of 1979), the Estate Duty (Distribution) Act, 1962 (9 of 1962) and the`
  line `Constitution (Distribution of Revenues) Order, 1985 in such manner as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39837)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Property, assets, rights, liabilities, obligations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39837&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) All such property and assets within the`
  line `existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh as are held immediately before the appointed day by the`
  line `Union for purposes of governance of that Union territory shall, on and from that day, pass to the State of`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh unless the purposes for which such property and assets are so held are Union`
  line `purposes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the cash balances in the treasuries in the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh`
  line `before the appointed day shall, as from that day, vest in the State of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) All rights, liabilities and obligations (other than those relatable to, or in connection with, a Union`
  line `purpose), whether arising out of any contract or otherwise, which are, immediately before the appointed`
  line day,—
  line
  line `(a) the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Central Government arising out of, or in`
  line `connection with, the governance of the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh; or`
  line
  line `(b) the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Administrator of the existing Union territory of`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh in his capacity as such, or of the Government of that Union territory,`
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day, be the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Government of the`
  line `State of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(3) The right to recover arrears of—`
  line
  line `(a) any tax or duty being a tax or duty enumerated in the State List in the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution; or`
  line
  line `(b) any duty referred to in article 268; or`
  line
  line `(c) any tax under the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956),`
  line
  line `which have fallen due in the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh, shall pass to the State of`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not apply to, or in relation to,—`
  line
  line `(a) any institution, undertaking or project the expenditure in relation to which is, immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, met from and out of the Consolidated Fund of India;`
  line
  line `(b) any property which has been placed by the Union at the disposal of the administration of the`
  line `existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh subject to the condition that the ownership thereof will`
  line `continue to vest in the Union.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "liability" includes liability in respect of any civil deposit, local fund deposit, charitable or`
  line `other endowment, provident fund account, pension or actionable wrong;`
  line
  line `(b) "Union purposes" means the purposes of Government relatable to any of the matters`
  line `mentioned in the Union List.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (39838)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Provision relating to All-India Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39838&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Indian Administrative Service,`
  line `the Indian Police Service and the Indian Forest Service who, immediately before the appointed day, is`
  line `holding any post in the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh shall, until otherwise directed by`
  line `the Central Government, be deemed to be on deputation, on and from the appointed day, to the`
  line `Government of the State of Arunachal Pradesh on the same terms and conditions of service as are`
  line `applicable to him under the relevant cadre rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of such deputation shall in no case extend beyond a period of three years`
  line `from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "cadre rules" means the Indian Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules,`
  line `1954, the Indian Police Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954 or the Indian Forest Service (Cadre) Rules, 1966, as`
  line `the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (39839)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Provisions relating to other services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39839&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who immediately before the appointed`
  line `day is serving in connection with the affairs of the Union under the administrative control of the`
  line `Administrator of the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh shall, unless otherwise directed by an`
  line `order of the Central Government, be deemed to have been allocated for service as from that day in`
  line `connection with the affairs of the State of Arunachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided that no directions shall be issued under this section after the expiry of a period of one year`
  line `from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall not apply in relation to persons to whom the provisions of`
  line `section 35 apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (39840)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Other provisions as to services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39840&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this section or section 36 shall be deemed to`
  line `affect on or after the appointed day, the operation of the provisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of the`
  line `Constitution in relation to determination of the conditions of service of persons serving in connection with`
  line `the affairs of the State of Arunachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day in the case of`
  line `any person referred to in section 36 shall not be varied to his disadvantage except with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) All services prior to the appointed day rendered by a person deemed to have been allocated under`
  line `section 36 in connection with the administration of the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the affairs of the State of Arunachal Pradesh`
  line `for the purposes of the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (39841)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Provisions as to continuance of officers in same posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39841&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Every person who, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh shall continue to hold the same post or office and`
  line `shall be deemed, on and from that day, to have been duly appointed to the post or office by the`
  line `Government of, or other appropriate authority in, the State of Arunachal Pradesh on the same terms and`
  line `conditions of appointment and on the same tenure as he was holding the post or office immediately before`
  line `that day:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority on or after the`
  line `appointed day from passing in relation to such person any order affecting his continuance in such post or`
  line office.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (39842)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39842&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order, establish one or more Advisory`
  line `Committees for the purpose of assisting it in regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the discharge of its functions under this Part; and`
  line
  line `(b) the ensuring of fair and equitable treatment to all persons affected by the provisions of this`
  line `Part and the proper consideration of any representations made by such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (39843)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Prohibition of representation after certain period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39843&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any law or rule for the time being in force, no representation shall lie against any order`
  line `passed under the provisions of this Part on the expiry of three months from the date of publication or`
  line `service, whichever is earlier, of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, suo motu or otherwise and for reasons to be recorded, reopen any matter and pass such orders thereon as may appear to it to be appropriate if it is satisfied that it`
  line `is necessary so to do in order to prevent any miscarriage of justice to any affected person.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (39844)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of Central Government to give direcions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39844&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to the Government of the State of Arunachal Pradesh as may appear to it to be necessary for the`
  line `purpose of giving effect to the foregoing provisions of this Part and the State Government shall comply`
  line `with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (39845)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title [Repealed].
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39845&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of article 210, article 239A and article 240 of the Constitution].—Rep. by the`
  line `Repealing and Amending Act, 2001 (30 of 2001), s. 2 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (39846)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title [Repealed].
  content `[Amendment of Act 28 of 1958].—Rep. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39846&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (39847)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title [Repealed].
  content `[Amendment of Act 20 of 1963].—Rep. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39847&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (39848)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title [Repealed].
  content `[Amendment of Act 84 of 1971].—Rep. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39848&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (39849)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Continuance of existing laws and their adaptations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39849&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) All laws in force, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, in the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh shall continue to be in force in the`
  line `State of Arunachal Pradesh until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other`
  line `competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of Arunachal Pradesh of any`
  line `law made before the appointed day, the appropriate Government may, within two years from that day, by`
  line `order, make such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as`
  line `may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations`
  line `and modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other`
  line `competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means, as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, the Central`
  line `Government and as respects any other law, the Government of the State of Arunachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (39850)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39850&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made under section 46 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or`
  line `authority required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application in`
  line `relation to the State of Arunachal Pradesh, construe the law in such manner not affecting the substance as`
  line `may be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (39851)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Provisions as to continuance of courts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39851&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `All courts and tribunals and all authorities`
  line `discharging lawful functions throughout the existing Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh or any part`
  line `thereof immediately before the appointed day shall, unless their continuance is inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act or until other provision is made by a competent Legislature or other competent`
  line `authority, continue to exercise their respective functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (39852)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Effect of provisions of Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39852&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (39853)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39853&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of three years from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (39854)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057&sectionId=39854&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00055_198669_1517807327057
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
